---
title: Deadlock-Safe Lock Acquisition
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Agent
    participant C as Coordinator
    participant B as Agent B (holder)

    Note over A,B: Locks sorted lexicographically to prevent deadlocks
    A->>A: Sort: [api:/v1/users, db:schema:users, src/api/users.py]

    A->>C: acquire_lock("api:/v1/users")
    C-->>A: acquired

    A->>C: acquire_lock("db:schema:users")
    C-->>A: acquired

    A->>C: acquire_lock("src/api/users.py")
    C-->>A: CONFLICT (held by Agent B)

    Note over A,C: Rollback ALL locks in reverse order
    A->>C: release_lock("db:schema:users")
    A->>C: release_lock("api:/v1/users")

    Note over A: Exponential backoff + jitter (max 3 retries)
    A->>A: wait 2s + random jitter

    A->>C: acquire_lock("api:/v1/users")
    C-->>A: acquired
    A->>C: acquire_lock("db:schema:users")
    C-->>A: acquired
    A->>C: acquire_lock("src/api/users.py")
    Note over B: Lock released
    C-->>A: acquired

    Note over A,C: All locks held - proceed with code generation
